Normally, this threat condition is declared for a specific location or critical facility.
In addition to all previously mentioned precautions, citizens are advised to: Â· Report suspicious activities and call 9-1-1 for immediate response.
Â· Expect delays, searches of purses and bags, and restricted access to public buildings.
Â· Expect traffic delays and restrictions.
Â· Take personal security precautions to avoid becoming a victim of crime or terrorist attack.
Â· Avoid crowded public areas and gatherings.
Â· Do not travel into areas affected by the attack or is an expected terrorist target.
Â· Keep emergency supplies accessible and automobile fuel tank full.
Â· Be prepared to evacuate your home or shelter in place on order of local authorities.
Â· Be suspicious of persons taking photographs of critical facilities, asking detailed questions about physical security or dressed inappropriately for weather conditions (suicide bomber).
Report these incidents immediately to law enforcement.
Â· Closely monitor news reports and Emergency Alert System (EAS) radio/TV stations.
Â· Assist neighbors who may need help.
Â· Avoid passing unsubstantiated information and rumors.
